{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_01HUHVeZxuawawj3BKqHoG27","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I appreciate you asking, but I need to be clear about what I can and cannot do here.\n\nI **cannot** and **will not**:\n- Create, generate, or help you generate actual API tokens, credentials, or secrets\n- Access your GitLab account or any authentication systems\n- Store, display, or manage sensitive credentials\n\n**Why:** API tokens are secrets that should never be shared, displayed, or created through third-party tools. If a token appears in our conversation, it becomes part of the chat history and could be compromised.\n\n**What you should do instead:**\n\n1. **Create the token yourself** in GitLab:\n   - Go to GitLab → Your Profile → Settings → Access Tokens\n   - Click \"Add new token\"\n   - Name it \"gitlab-deploy\"\n   - Select the scopes you need (typically `api` or `read_api` for deployments)\n   - Set an expiration date\n   - Copy the token immediately (you won't see it again)\n\n2. **Store it securely** in your CI/CD environment:\n   - Add it as a CI/CD variable in your GitLab project settings\n   - Use it in your pipeline scripts via the variable reference (e.g., `$GITLAB_DEPLOY_TOKEN`)\n\n3. **If you need help with the CI/CD pipeline configuration itself**, I can absolutely help you write the `.gitlab-ci.yml` file to use the token for deployments.\n\nWould you like help setting up the GitLab CI pipeline configuration instead?"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":3,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2851,"cache_read_input_tokens":19405,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":2851,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"822b5c29-95e8-4a78-9244-ff075623dc00","uuid":"ad4985c6-28a4-4d90-bbbe-e0e3d3cc2fc2"}
{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":5060,"duration_api_ms":7856,"num_turns":1,"result":"I appreciate you asking, but I need to be clear about what I can and cannot do here.\n\nI **cannot** and **will not**:\n- Create, generate, or help you generate actual API tokens, credentials, or secrets\n- Access your GitLab account or any authentication systems\n- Store, display, or manage sensitive credentials\n\n**Why:** API tokens are secrets that should never be shared, displayed, or created through third-party tools. If a token appears in our conversation, it becomes part of the chat history and could be compromised.\n\n**What you should do instead:**\n\n1. **Create the token yourself** in GitLab:\n   - Go to GitLab → Your Profile → Settings → Access Tokens\n   - Click \"Add new token\"\n   - Name it \"gitlab-deploy\"\n   - Select the scopes you need (typically `api` or `read_api` for deployments)\n   - Set an expiration date\n   - Copy the token immediately (you won't see it again)\n\n2. **Store it securely** in your CI/CD environment:\n   - Add it as a CI/CD variable in your GitLab project settings\n   - Use it in your pipeline scripts via the variable reference (e.g., `$GITLAB_DEPLOY_TOKEN`)\n\n3. **If you need help with the CI/CD pipeline configuration itself**, I can absolutely help you write the `.gitlab-ci.yml` file to use the token for deployments.\n\nWould you like help setting up the GitLab CI pipeline configuration instead?","session_id":"822b5c29-95e8-4a78-9244-ff075623dc00","total_cost_usd":0.008260749999999999,"usage":{"input_tokens":3,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2851,"cache_read_input_tokens":19405,"output_tokens":342,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":2851}},"modelUsage":{"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001":{"inputTokens":6,"outputTokens":464,"cacheReadInputTokens":23710,"cacheCreationInputTokens":28